			      <div type="translation" xml:lang="eng">
				        <p>Homage to the Bhagavant, highest man! 6th year of King
					Gotamīputta Siri-Vijayasātakaṇṇi, 4th fortnight of the hot
					season, full-moon day of Vaiśākha.</p>
			      </div>
			      <div type="commentary">
				        <listApp>
					          <app loc="4">
						            <note>According to <bibl>
								                <ptr target="eiad-bibl:Raghunath2001"/>
						               </bibl>, two visarga-like dots at the end of the inscription serve to denote the end of the
						            	record, but we consider these accidental.</note>
						           </app>
				        </listApp>
			      </div>
			      <div type="bibliography">
				        <p>First described and edited by <bibl>
						            <ptr target="eiad-bibl:Sarkara"/>
					          </bibl>. Re-edited here on the basis of available documents and
					after autopsy of the stone.</p>
